cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NI 

The paper deals with the intersection of distributed computing and game theory, specifically studying the convergence of simple heuristics in dynamic environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also touches on social networks and routing, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), respectively.
